👉 Do NOT keep Replit’s auto-generated SESSION_SECRET
👉 Replace it with your own (the one used in production earlier)

🧠 Why this matters (very important)

SESSION_SECRET is used for:

Signing cookies

Session validation

Auth integrity

If you change it:

👉 All existing sessions become invalid
👉 Users get logged out
👉 In some cases → auth bugs / “invalid session” errors

✅ What YOU should do
✔️ If this is a migration of existing app (your case)

👉 Use the SAME secret as before

So:

Delete Replit’s auto-generated SESSION_SECRET

Add your original one

✔️ If you don’t care about existing sessions

(early-stage app / no users yet)

👉 You can keep Replit’s one

But consistency is still better.

🔥 Best Practice (production mindset)

Always control secrets yourself:

Never rely on:

Auto-generated values

Platform defaults

Instead:

Define in .env.example:

SESSION_SECRET=your_strong_secret_here
⚠️ One more important thing (many people miss this)

Make sure:

👉 Same secret is used across:

Backend

Any worker / cron service

Any auth service

Otherwise:
👉 Session mismatch → random logout issues

🧠 Rule of Thumb
Scenario	What to do
Migrating existing app	✅ Use OLD secret
New app, no users	😐 Either is fine
Production system	✅ Always control manually
💡 Pro Tip (security)

Your secret should be:

Long (at least 32+ chars)

Random

Example:

k8s@92Jsl_!xPqZ7#LmT$w8vR2@aN9dE6
